view.name: Biennial Operating Budget
view.description: Biennial Operating Budget.  This includes the Year 1 Revised Budget and Year 2 Adopted Budget.  Includes operating budget expenditures and revenues only.  Does not include capital expenditures (CIP).

columns.name: Ledger Type
columns.description:
General Ledger Description for the posting to the ledger.

Ledger Types are as follows:
B1 = Revised Budget
BA =  Adopted Budget
B2 = Estimated Actual (not used in this report)
AA = Actuals

columns.name: Cost Center Type
columns.description:
This field identifies expenses and budget between operating and capital.
IS = Operating
JB = Capital

columns.name: Fund ID
columns.description: This is the Fund Number.

columns.name: Fund Name
columns.description: This is Fund Name associated with the Fund Number.

columns.name: Department ID
columns.description:
This is the department number.  Each department has an assigned number.

Non-Departmental is used for non-department specific transfers (interfund transfers) and obligations (ex. debt service payments, pass- through payment).

columns.name: Department Name
columns.description: Department Name that corresponds to Department ID.

columns.name: Division ID
columns.description: This the division id within a department. Division id is unique to a department.   A division ID can be used across multiple funds.

columns.name: Division Name
columns.description: Division name corresponding to division id.

columns.name: Object
columns.description:
This is the object code that defines the specific line items.  They are generally unique to a line item.

Objects starting with 5 are expenses.

Objects starting with 4 are revenues.

columns.name: Object Description
columns.description: This description defines the object code.  Generally a description is unique to an object.  However, this is not always the case.

columns.name: Revenue Category Code
columns.description:
This is code identifies the revenue category as presented in the budget.  This does not apply to Expenditures.  Expenditures are categorized by object sequence (511000 - 511999 = salaries and wages and 520000 - 5889999 -= supplies and expenses.

These categories do not necessarily reflect the categories as presented in the CAFR.

columns.name: Category code description
columns.description: This corresponds to category code.

columns.name: Fiscal Year
columns.description: This defines the fiscal year . For ex: 2010 is FY July2010 - 2011.

columns.name: March

columns.description: Period 10. This is the month that entry was posted.

columns.name: June
columns.description: This is the final month of the fiscal year.  For this purposes of this report, it includes period 13.  Period 13 is the adjustment period for year-end CAFR related adjustments.
